                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Fragments of trabeation with parts of the upper moulded cornice, with inscribed face below, most likely from the external frieze of the north side of the portico of the bouleuterion. There seems little reason to doubt from the form and style that these are all fragments of the same inscription. Fragment (a) is W 30 x H 19.5 x D 17 cm; (b) is W 28.5 x H 9 x D 10.5 cm; (c) is W 41 x H 24.5 x D31.5; (d) is W 30.5 x H 20.5 x D 22.5 cm; fragment (e), two joining fragments, W 40.25 x H 21 x D 11 cm.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.limestone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html">limestone</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.arch_element.architrave">architrave</objectType>
                                    <dimensions><!--ISegesta-->
                                        <height unit="cm"></height>
                                        <width unit="cm"></width>
                                        <depth unit="cm"></depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.fragments.non-contiguous"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Part of a single line of large Greek letters</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.incomplete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Alpha with broken bar; Kappa with short arms; omicron slightly smaller and above the line; standard four-bar sigma with parallel top and bottom strokes. Fine v-cut letters</p><!--following ISegesta-->
                                <locus from="fr.a" to="fr.e">fragments a-e</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm">56-70</height>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <height unit="mm"/>
                                </dimensions>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
